Package com.ibm.team.build.common.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IBuildAction
    Represents a given action that can be performed on a build.
    IBuildActivity
    A build activity is a period of time during a build with a specific ID and a descriptive label.
    IBuildActivityId
    Represents the id of a build activity.
    IBuildAverageData
    Interface for accessing the averages available for a build definition.
    IBuildAverageDataHandle
    Handle for the averages available for a build definition.
    IBuildCategoryHandle
    A grouping of build results
    IBuildConfigurationElement
    Defines configuration data as part of a IBuildDefinition or IBuildEngine.
    IBuildDefinition
    The build definition is a primary identifier for a set of builds.
    IBuildDefinitionHandle
    Handle for a build definition.
    IBuildDefinitionInstance
    Represents a snapshot of a build definition at the moment the build request is made to preserve the state of that build definition to be used when the request is processed.
    IBuildEngine
    A definition for a build engine.
    IBuildEngineActivity
    Records the activity of the build engine in terms of the last time it contacted the repository.
    IBuildEngineActivityHandle
    Records the activity of the build engine handling requests.
    IBuildEngineHandle
    Definition for a build engine available on the network.
    IBuildFolder
    Represents a build folder used to categorize build items.
    IBuildFolderHandle
    Handle for a build folder.
    IBuildHistory
    The build history.
    IBuildItem
    The base interface for all team build item handles in the facade layer.
    IBuildItemHandle
    The base handle interface for all team build item handles in the facade layer.
    IBuildProperty
    Defines a name-value pair.
    IBuildRequest
    Represents a request to perform an action on a build result or build definition.
    IBuildRequestHandle
    Represents a request to perform an action on a build result or build definition.
    IBuildRequestParams
    Represents the parameters to the request build operation.
    IBuildRequestQueueHandle
    Represents a request to perform an action on a build or build definition.
    IBuildResult
    The result of a build.
    IBuildResultContribution
    A contribution to a build result.
    IBuildResultHandle
    The result of a build.
    IBuildResultPruningPolicy
    The build pruning policy.
    IBuildSchedule
    A build schedule.
    IBuildScheduleEntry
    A build schedule entry.
    ICompileContribution
    A compile contribution to a build result.
    ICompileContributionHandle
    Handle for a compile contribution.
    ICompileOutputFile
    A class representing a file generated by compiling a compile source.
    ICompilePackage
    A package of compile sources and/or sub compile packages
    ICompilePackageHandle
    Handle for a compile package
    ICompileProblem
    A compile problem representing a warning or error during the compilation.
    ICompileSource
    A compile source representing a single source file in the compilation data.
    IConfigurationProperty
    Defines a name-value pair for a build configuration element property.
    IContributionProperty

    IExpectedContribution

    IJUnitTestClassHandle

    IJUnitTestSuiteContribution
